Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Equilibrium and Density of the Binary System 1-Phenylethylamine + Toluene
Citation.sAbstract: Isobaric (p = 98.71 kPa) and isothermal (T = 363.15 K, 383.15 K) vapor-liquid equilibria, as well as densities at 298.15 K, have been measured for the system 1-phenylethylamine + toluene. Good predictions of the vapor-liquid equilibrium data by the UNIFAC model were confirmed.
